					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-567202#post-1687272</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-567202/the-smell-of-her-hair#post-1687272</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 16 Jan 2013 17:43:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>TroyL</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>451071</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Thanks for catching that.</p> <p>My intent here was actually to draw more attention to the reason the GOC is a necessary &quot;evil.&quot; This guy basically took a girl he thought was pretty and made her into what he wanted her to be. Think about that for a second. Someone looks at you and decides that you'd be a lot better if you were a Christian than a Jew. That sort of shallow, first glance, egomaniacal attitude that so many people have. &quot;If only she didn't have that mole.&quot; &quot;If only he was taller.&quot; &quot;She should lose weight.&quot;</p> <p><em>Only this guy made that happen.</em></p> <p>That's why we have the GOC, and that's why—in spite of their tendency to destroy rather than understand—they are an integral part of the Foundation universe.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-567202#post-1641092</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-567202/the-smell-of-her-hair#post-1641092</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 07 Dec 2012 06:07:47 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Heiden</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>310272</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;He remembered the first time he met her, their high school year, when he’d first discovered some things about himself, about how he looked at the world, and how much he wanted her. She’d been so shallow. So weak in mind and body. It had been easy to take her, mold her, help her to grow as she should have. She appreciated it, of course. He made sure she did.&quot;</p> <p>Thank God for the GOC. +1.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
